      <div class="fq-q">Is the Viking Ship Museum open?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">No. The Viking Ship Museum (Vikingskipshuset) at Bygdøy has been closed since September 2021 for a full rebuild. It will reopen as the Museum of the Viking Age (Vikingtidsmuseet) in 2027. No part of the Bygdøy construction site is accessible to visitors. Any ticket sold for this venue before 2027 is not valid for entry.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Where can I see Viking ships in Oslo right now?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">The three Viking ships — Oseberg, Gokstad, and Tune — are not on public display during the construction period. Viking Age objects from the collection can currently be viewed at the Historical Museum (Historisk museum) at Frederiks gate 2 in central Oslo. Check historiskmuseum.no for current opening hours and admission prices.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">When will the Museum of the Viking Age open?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">The Museum of the Viking Age (Vikingtidsmuseet) is scheduled to open in 2027 at the same Bygdøy site. The new building will house the Oseberg, Gokstad, and Tune ships alongside over 5,500 other Viking Age objects. Sign up for updates at vikingtidsmuseet.no.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">What happened to the Oseberg, Gokstad, and Tune ships?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">All three ships were physically moved from the old Viking Ship Museum into the new Museum of the Viking Age building during 2025–2026. The Tune ship completed its transfer in February 2026. As of 25 February 2026, all three ships are confirmed safely installed in the new building. The fragile Oseberg burial sledges began their relocation in March 2026.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">How do I get to the Historical Museum in Oslo?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">The Historical Museum (Historisk museum) is at Frederiks gate 2, Oslo. It is a 10-minute walk from Oslo Central Station (Oslo S), or accessible by tram and bus lines to Nationaltheatret. Operated by the Museum of Cultural History, University of Oslo. Check historiskmuseum.no for current hours before visiting.</div>
    </div>
